name: Sugar & Spice Boutique
directions: Next to the Penthouse Club, near Pop's and The Oz
comment: Trans*- and queer-friendly adult shop (they even have binders, packers and other transitional apparel); two non-gendered single-stall restrooms.  Open floor plan makes easy navigation for wheelchairs or other mobility devices.

name: NE Seattle Tool Library
directions: At the south end

name: Kroger

name: Shields Building

name: Pure XHale

name: Crazy for Ewe Yarns

name: Adventure Science Center

name: 76 gas

name: Starbucks

name: Embassy Suites Hotels by Hilton, Concord
directions: From the main lobby head to the pool. The bathrooms here have been converted into gender neutral family stalls with locks.
comment: Restrooms used to be gendered. Make sure no one else is in the room bc some guests don't notice/care to lock the doors. Left side has a stall and a urinal. Right side has two stalls with feminine product bins. Both are unisex restrooms. with baby changing stations and locks on the door

name: Target
directions: Immediately to the left when you walk in
comment: Target has repeatedly asserted that people have the right to use the bathroom of their preference. There are gendered bathrooms with stalls. I think they also have a family bathroom? It probably looks good if you pretend to browse for a bit - the $3 section is also right by the doors!

name: San Joaquin General Hospital
directions: 2nd floor, 3 restrooms. 2 in short stay, one in the halway before  ICU
